  "text": "## Kubernetes RBAC Verb Coverage Audit Findings\n\n### Overview\nThis audit comprehensively identifies all Go source files in Kubernetes that define and enforce RBAC verb constraints. The analysis covers verb definitions, validation logic, authorization enforcement, and special verb handling.\n\n### Core Verb Definitions\n\nThe fundamental RBAC verb handling is defined in the following files:\n\n1. **Type Definitions (Verb Constants)**:\n   - `pkg/apis/rbac/types.go` (kubernetes/kubernetes): Defines `VerbAll = \"*\"` constant for allowing all verbs\n   - `staging/src/k8s.io/api/rbac/v1/types.go` and `v1alpha1/types.go`, `v1beta1/types.go` (kubernetes/kubernetes): Define the same constants in different API versions\n   - `rbac/v1/types.go`, `v1alpha1/types.go`, `v1beta1/types.go` (kubernetes/api): API library versions with identical verb constant definitions\n\n2. **Standard Verb Sets**:\n   - `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go` (lines 36-44) defines the standard Kubernetes verb groupings:\n     - **Write** = [\"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"]\n     - **ReadWrite** = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"]\n     - **Read** = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n     - **ReadUpdate** = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n\n### Verb Matching and Enforcement\n\n3. **Verb Matching Functions**:\n   - `pkg/apis/rbac/v1/evaluation_helpers.go`: Contains `VerbMatches()` function that performs the core verb matching logic:\n     - Checks if a rule verb equals `VerbAll` (\"*\")\n     - Checks if a rule verb matches the requested verb exactly\n   - `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go`: The `RuleAllows()` function uses `VerbMatches()` as the first constraint when evaluating if a rule permits a request\n\n4. **Verb Constraint Validation**:\n   - `pkg/apis/rbac/helpers.go` (lines 186-200): Critical validation enforcing that certain verbs cannot be combined with ResourceNames:\n     - Verbs \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"deletecollection\" are explicitly blacklisted when ResourceNames are specified\n     - This prevents illogical RBAC rules like \"get this specific pod with list verb\"\n   - `pkg/apis/rbac/v1/helpers.go`: Provides similar verb validation in the v1 API layer\n\n5. **Policy Rule Validation**:\n   - `pkg/apis/rbac/validation/validation.go` (function `ValidatePolicyRule`): Validates that:\n     - At least one verb must be present in a PolicyRule\n     - Resource rules and non-resource rules are mutually exclusive\n     - API groups are required for resource rules\n\n### Authorization and Rule Evaluation\n\n6. **RBAC Authorization Engine**:\n   - `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go`: The main RBAC authorizer that:\n     - Implements `Authorize()` method checking `RuleAllows()` for verb matching\n     - Provides `RulesFor()` method returning all applicable PolicyRules for a user\n     - Extracts verbs from PolicyRule.Verbs field during authorization decisions\n\n7. **Rule Resolution and Escalation Checks**:\n   - `pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go`: \n     - `ConfirmNoEscalation()` ensures users cannot grant permissions they don't have\n     - Uses `validation.Covers()` to check if user's verbs cover the verbs being assigned\n   - `pkg/registry/rbac/escalation_check.go`:\n     - Defines special verbs: \"escalate\" (for modifying roles) and \"bind\" (for creating role bindings)\n     - These special verbs enforce separation of duties in RBAC\n\n### Verb Coverage Analysis\n\n8. **Policy Comparator (Verb Coverage Logic)**:\n   - `staging/src/k8s.io/component-helpers/auth/rbac/validation/policy_comparator.go`:\n     - `Covers()` function determines if one set of rules fully covers another\n     - `BreakdownRule()` breaks rules into atomic verbs for comparison\n     - `ruleCovers()` (lines 158-173) checks if an owner rule's verbs cover servant rule's verbs:\n       - Line 159: `verbMatches := has(ownerRule.Verbs, rbacv1.VerbAll) || hasAll(ownerRule.Verbs, subRule.Verbs)`\n       - Ensures \"*\" wildcard verb covers all specific verbs\n\n### API Documentation\n\n9. **Authorization API Types**:\n   - `pkg/apis/authorization/types.go` (line 78): Documents standard Kubernetes verbs in ResourceAttributes:\n     - Comment: \"get, list, watch, create, update, delete, proxy. \\\"*\\\" means all.\"\n\n### Bootstrap Policies\n\n10. **Default RBAC Policies**:\n    - `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go`: Uses the verb constants (Read, Write, ReadWrite, ReadUpdate) to define default ClusterRoles for system components\n    - `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/controller_policy.go`: Defines controller-specific verb permissions\n    - `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/namespace_policy.go`: Defines namespace-scoped role permissions\n\n### Summary of Verb Enforcement Chain\n\nThe complete verb enforcement chain flows as:\n1. **Definition** → Constants in types.go files\n2. **Validation** → helpers.go enforces ResourceNames constraints; validation.go checks rule structure\n3. **Matching** → VerbMatches() in evaluation_helpers.go performs exact or wildcard matching\n4. **Authorization** → RuleAllows() in rbac.go uses VerbMatches() to evaluate requests\n5. **Escalation** → escalation_check.go handles special \"escalate\" and \"bind\" verbs\n6. **Coverage** → policy_comparator.go ensures verb coverage when checking permission inheritance\n\n### Completeness Assessment\n\nAll API handlers enforce verb constraints through the centralized `RuleAllows()` function in the RBAC authorizer. Every request goes through this function which invokes `VerbMatches()`. The explicit enforcement that verbs like \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", and \"deletecollection\" cannot be used with ResourceNames (in pkg/apis/rbac/helpers.go) ensures logical consistency. The standard verb sets defined in bootstrappolicy/policy.go (Read, Write, ReadWrite, ReadUpdate) provide the de facto standard for Kubernetes verb groupings.\n"
